1.0 Whom does the policy cover?
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
The holder of a valid MasterCard Business Gold card issued by
&BANKNAVN., as well as his/her spouse/life partner who is travelling
with him/her:
.of 5mm
*¤The cardholder's partner must live at the same address as the cardholder
to be included in the coverage.
.of 5mm
*¤The cardholder's spouse is covered, even though he/she may not live at
the same address as the cardholder.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Any children of the cardholder and his/her spouse/partner are covered
according to the following rules, when such children are travelling
together with the cardholder:
.br
.of 5mm
*¤Children of the cardholder and his/her spouse/partner are covered up
until the age of 21, irrespective of their address.
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Children of the cardholder and his/her spouse/partner are covered when
said children share the same address as the cardholder, irrespective of
their age.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In this context, 'life partner' is taken to mean a person who lives with
the cardholder in a marriage-like relationship, and who, for at least six
months prior to the insurance event, has shared an address with the
cardholder.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
1.1 The insurance coverage also applies if the cardholder has a MasterCard
Business Gold card and lives abroad.
.kp on
4.2.7 In the event of death, payment is made to the closest
relative(s). In this context, 'the closest relative(s)' is
taken to mean the insured's spouse or, if the insured
is not married, his/her life partner with whom he/she has shared
an address for at least six months.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the insured has neither a spouse nor a life partner, payment will be
made to his/her children. If the insured does not have a spouse/partner or
children, the sum payable on death is limited to DKK 12,000.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.2 Disability compensation is payable when an accident has
resulted in permanent medical disability of at least 5%, and the
condition is stationary. Compensation is payable up to three years
from the date of the injury. If the condition is not stationary at
this time, the compensation payable will be determined on the basis
of the condition at this time, irrespective of whether the condition
becomes stationary at a later date, involving a greater or lesser
degree of disability.
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.3 The insurance sum payable amounts to DKK 750,000 in the case of
complete disability (100%). The compensation payable amounts to the
percentage of the maximum insurance sum that corresponds to the
established degree of disability.
.br
The degree of disability shall be determined in accordance with the
disability table that the National Board of Industrial Injuries in
Denmark applies at the time of the injury. If the degree of
disability cannot be directly established using the disability table
applied by the National Board of Industrial Injuries in Denmark, the
injured party's degree of medical disability shall be determined
using principles corresponding to those on which the disability table
is based, according to the level of physical functional impairment.
.br
In all cases, the degree of disability will be established on a
purely medical basis, irrespective of any reduction in earning
capacity, the particular profession of the injured party or other
individual conditions. Loss of earning capacity is not covered.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.4 The degree of disability cannot exceed 100%.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.5 An existing disability cannot result in the compensation payable
being set higher than if no such disability had existed.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.6 Up to DKK 10,000 is payable in compensation for treatment of acute
dental damage arising during the period of travel as a result of an
accident. The dental treatment must have commenced abroad, but may, if
necessary, be completed once the injured party has returned to his/her
country of residence.
